2.Demonstrate setting up a single-node, single-broker Kafka cluster and show basic operations such as creating topics and producing/consuming messages.

Start Kafka Broker
Open a Command prompt change to kafka directory and run the following command:
.\bin\windows\zookeeper-server-start.bat .\config\zookeeper.properties

Now open a new terminal and run the following command:
.\bin\windows\kafka-server-start.bat  .\config\server.properties

Create a Topic:
•	To create a new topic, run the following command:
bin\windows\kafka-topics.bat --create  --topic my-topic --replication-factor 1 --partitions 1 --bootstrap-server localhost:9092
 
Note: We can create any number of partitions depending upon requirement. The replication factor can never be greater than the number of available brokers.

Describe Topic: To describe a topic within the broker, use '--describe' command as:
bin\windows\kafka-topics.bat --describe --topic my-topic --bootstrap-server localhost:9092
  
Produce Messages:
•	Create a console-based Kafka producer to send messages tothe message Kafka topic running at “localhost:9092”. To do this, open a new terminal and run the following command::

bin\windows\kafka-console-producer.bat --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --topic my-topic
A '>' will appear in the new line. Start producing some messages, as shown below:
 

Consume Messages:
o	Create a console-based Kafka consumer to retrieve messages from the message Kafka topic running at localhost:9092. To do this, open a new terminal and run the following command:
bin\windows\kafka-console-consumer.bat --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --topic my-topic --from-beginning

 


